        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-30T04:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-30T04:35:00-05:00" n="1337" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1337">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.24591/7–3045: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 1337<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Iran</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MW2" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Murray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-30T13:00:00+03:25">July 30, 1945—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>560. <persName corresp="#p_BBGDP1">Booth</persName> has received further
                        telegram<note n="1" xml:id="d1337fn1">Not printed.</note> from Potsdam
                    canceling <gloss target="#t_War1">War</gloss> telegram reported <gloss target="#t_mytel1">mytel</gloss> 554 July 28<note n="2" xml:id="d1337fn2">
                        <ref target="#d1335">Document No. 1335</ref>.</note> and authorizing more
                    gradual withdrawal troops from Iran. He is now instructed transfer HQ
                    (headquarters) from Amirabad to Khorramshahr by October 1 but to leave custodial
                    detachment at Amirabad. Orders state <gloss target="#t_OANLC1">OANLC</gloss>
                    (Office Army Navy Liquidation Commissioner]) staff will remain here.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MW2">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Murray</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
